Samuel Nnaemeka Anyagafu, 58, of Ururo Village in Umunze, Orumba-South Local Government Area of Anambra State, who died on June 16, 2019, during a brief illness in Lagos, would be buried on Thursday, December 19. Lying in state takes place same day and would be followed by interment in his family compound in Ururo after funeral rites. Entertainment of guests follows immediately after interment. He is survived by wife, Vera, children, brothers and sisters, among other relatives.